               limits?

               Despite appearances the limit still doesn’t care about what the function is doing at    = −2. In
               this case the function that we’ve got is simply “nice enough” so that what is happening around
               the point is exactly the same as what is happening at the point. Eventually we will formalize up
               just what is meant by “nice enough”. At this point let’s not worry too much about what “nice
               enough” is. Let’s just take advantage of the fact that some functions will be “nice enough”,
               whatever that means.



